refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.parameters;
codepoint
&intl.codepoint.parameter;
nameChoice
Which set of names to use for the lookup. Can be any of these constants:
IntlChar::UNICODE_CHAR_NAME (default) IntlChar::UNICODE_10_CHAR_NAME IntlChar::EXTENDED_CHAR_NAME IntlChar::CHAR_NAME_ALIAS IntlChar::CHAR_NAME_CHOICE_COUNT

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 The corresponding name, or an empty string if there is no name for this character,
 or &null; if there is no such code point.

  &reftitle.examples;

   &intl.codepoint.example;


<?php
var_dump(IntlChar::charName("."));
var_dump(IntlChar::charName(".", IntlChar::UNICODE_CHAR_NAME));
var_dump(IntlChar::charName("\u{2603}"));
var_dump(IntlChar::charName("\u{0000}"));
?>


   &example.outputs;


string(9) "FULL STOP"
string(9) "FULL STOP"
string(7) "SNOWMAN"
string(0) ""
